hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Mass conservation of the mixture:
   $$A_1\,j_1 = A_2\,j_2\;\Longrightarrow\;j_2 = \sigma\,j_1,\quad\sigma \equiv \frac{A_1}{A_2}.$$
2. Mass conservation of the gas phase:
   $$A_1\,j_{g1} = A_2\,j_{g2}\;\Longrightarrow\;j_{g2} = \sigma\,j_{g1}.$$
3. Drift-flux relations at stations 1 and 2:
   $$j_{g1} = \alpha_1\bigl(C_0\,j_1+v_{gj}\bigr),\qquad 
     j_{g2} = \alpha_2\bigl(C_0\,j_2+v_{gj}\bigr).$$
4. Combine gas continuity with drift-flux:
   $$\alpha_2\bigl(C_0\,j_2+v_{gj}\bigr)
     = \sigma\,\alpha_1\bigl(C_0\,j_1+v_{gj}\bigr)
     \;\Longrightarrow\;
     \frac{\alpha_2}{\alpha_1}
     = \sigma\;\frac{C_0\,j_1+v_{gj}}{C_0\,j_2+v_{gj}}
     = \sigma\;\frac{C_0\,j_1+v_{gj}}{C_0\,\sigma\,j_1+v_{gj}}.$$
5. Apply the critical-flow condition 
   $$j_1 = \frac{v_{gj}}{C_0-1}.$$
   Then
   $$
   C_0\,j_1+v_{gj}
   = \frac{C_0\,v_{gj}}{C_0-1}+v_{gj}
   = \frac{2C_0-1}{C_0-1}\,v_{gj},$$
   $$
   C_0\,\sigma\,j_1+v_{gj}
   = \frac{C_0\,\sigma\,v_{gj}}{C_0-1}+v_{gj}
   = \frac{C_0(\sigma+1)-1}{C_0-1}\,v_{gj}.$$
6. Substitute and simplify (canceling common factors $(C_0-1)$ and $v_{gj}$):
   $$
   \frac{\alpha_2}{\alpha_1}
   = \sigma\;\frac{\displaystyle\frac{2C_0-1}{C_0-1}\,v_{gj}}
                   {\displaystyle\frac{C_0(\sigma+1)-1}{C_0-1}\,v_{gj}}
   = \frac{\sigma\,(2C_0-1)}{\,C_0(\sigma+1)-1\,}.
   $$
